|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOWayshards are towering ancient crystals found across the world, one
linked to each charted area. A shard remembers every traveler who has
touched it, and together the shards form a fast travel network.

Attuning: find a wayshard and |YKBtouch shard|YKO. The first touch attunes
you to it as the shard learns your touch. Look at a shard to see
whether it already knows you. Ghosts cannot touch the shards, and they
will not answer during or shortly after combat.

New adventurers: characters up to level 10 automatically know the
wayshards of the newbie areas.

Traveling: at any wayshard, |YKBtouch shard|YKO again to see your possible
destinations, grouped by world and region with a level range for each.
Each destination has a stable waymark ID. Choose with |YKBtravel <id>|YKO or
|YKBtravel <area>|YKO, or |YKBcancel|YKO to dismiss the menu. Anywhere at all,
|YKBwaypoints|YKO lists every shard you have attuned to; entries marked
unavailable are known to you but cannot currently be used for fast travel.

Costs and limits:

  - Travel costs nothing, but the shards need a minute to settle: you
    must wait 60 seconds between trips.
  - A shard can only reach other attuned shards on the same planet.
  - You cannot depart while fighting, shortly after combat, as a
    ghost, or from places that dampen teleportation.

Wayshards look different from world to world -- deep violet in
Darkwind, frost-blue in Hyperborea, sea-green in Souvrael, and more --
but all of them answer to a touch.|XX0

